JUNETEENTH (6/19), celebrating the end of slavery in the US, was initially observed in Texas in 1866, after President Lincoln's Emancipation Proclamation in 1862. President Biden declared Juneteenth a federal holiday in 2021, celebrating freedom & the triumph of the human spirit. https://t.co/xaLsTjJDos
